'''Terrence "TC" Carson''' is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] voice actor.

==Biography==
As a voice actor, he portrayed [[Mace Windu]] in a variety of prequel-era ''Star Wars'' projects, including ''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds: Clone Campaigns]]'', ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'', the [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (video game)|''Clone Wars'']] video game, the [[Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith (video game)|''Revenge of the Sith'']] video game, [[Star Wars: Clone Wars|the animated ''Clone Wars'' cartoon]] (where he also voiced [[Saesee Tiin/Legends|Saesee Tiin]] and [[Oro Dassyne/Legends|Oro Dassyne]]), and most recently [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars|''The Clone Wars'' TV series]], ''[[Star Wars Battlefront: Elite Squadron]]'', and ''[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi (television series)|Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi]]''. He is the official "audio double" for the character portrayed by [[Samuel L. Jackson]].

